  "text": "In C11 (127-322 %), respectively, and decreased the concentrations of total N, NH 4 -N, NO 3 -N, and total P by 0.8-2.2 lg L -1 (0.2-0.4 %), 1.5-5.2 lg L -1 (10-32 %), 0.7-9.6 lg L -1 (2-22 %), and 0.6-1.6 lg L -1 (5-11 %), (1992 [CITATION_1] ( ) C34 (1992 [CITATION_2] ( ) C11 (1992 [CITATION_3] ( ) Ref (1992 [CITATION_4] ( ) C8 (1992 [CITATION_5] Total N (lg L (72) 311 (48) 385 (73) 403 (77) 422 (70) Total N (kg ha -1 year respectively, but did not affect PO 4 -P concentrations (Figs. 4, 5) . Changes in NO 3 -N were significant already in the second year after clear-cutting, whereas significant changes in the concentrations of other substances were not observed until minimum 4 years after clear-cutting. In C8, clear-cutting increased SS concentrations by 0.3-2.1 mg L -1 (92-435 %) but did not affect significantly the concentrations of other substances (Figs. 4, 5 ).",
